1
00:00:01,549 --> 00:00:02,520
Instructor: Right now,

2
00:00:02,520 --> 00:00:05,040
one thing that we have to do in a hacky way

3
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:09,450
is whenever a user logs in and we land on the HOME page,

4
00:00:09,450 --> 00:00:13,800
we are getting the session here and we are setting that.

5
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:16,980
But what if we do not want that hacky way?

6
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:20,250
What if we want the page model in _layout

7
00:00:20,250 --> 00:00:22,500
where it is getting the shopping cart,

8
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:25,140
it should automatically check all of that,

9
00:00:25,140 --> 00:00:27,600
and if it does not have a value,

10
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,580
it should go to the database

11
00:00:29,580 --> 00:00:31,863
and find out the count on its own?

12
00:00:32,790 --> 00:00:36,120
So here, we are talking about having a page model

13
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:40,248
or rather a backend file for _layout.

14
00:00:40,248 --> 00:00:44,610
Now, that is not technically possible with _layout,

15
00:00:44,610 --> 00:00:46,770
but we have something special

16
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:49,920
which can accomplish the same functionality,

17
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:52,537
and that is view component.

18
00:00:52,537 --> 00:00:55,440
Now, typically, I explain what something is

19
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:56,910
before we program,

20
00:00:56,910 --> 00:00:59,730
but view component is one of those things

21
00:00:59,730 --> 00:01:03,090
where we have some configuration that we have to do,

22
00:01:03,090 --> 00:01:07,230
but after that is done, everything will come together.

23
00:01:07,230 --> 00:01:10,440
It is one of the advanced concepts in MVC,

24
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:12,510
so make sure to follow along

25
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:16,201
because there is some syntax that you have to follow.

26
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:20,940
Now, view component is exactly similar to a partial view.

27
00:01:20,940 --> 00:01:24,570
But the difference here is your model or partial view

28
00:01:24,570 --> 00:01:28,140
will have a page model or a code behind file

29
00:01:28,140 --> 00:01:31,263
where you can do some programmings for your UI.

30
00:01:32,545 --> 00:01:35,520
But if you are working with partial view,

31
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:38,091
you do not have a page model.

32
00:01:38,091 --> 00:01:40,380
In order to get started,

33
00:01:40,380 --> 00:01:43,650
where we have our main web project here,

34
00:01:43,650 --> 00:01:46,980
inside there, I will create a new folder,

35
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:50,759
and I will have to stop the application, of course,

36
00:01:50,759 --> 00:01:55,092
and we will rename that to be ViewComponents.

37
00:01:55,092 --> 00:01:59,610
Inside that folder, we will be adding our view components

38
00:01:59,610 --> 00:02:02,760
which will basically be a Class file.

39
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:05,040
Now, we can call this anything we want

40
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:08,400
like in our case it is a shopping cart count,

41
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,919
so we can call it ShoppingCart.

42
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:12,450
But after that file,

43
00:02:12,450 --> 00:02:17,040
we have to append a special word which is ViewComponent,

44
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:19,980
and then we will add .cs.

45
00:02:19,980 --> 00:02:24,450
That is a keyword that is needed for view component.

46
00:02:24,450 --> 00:02:26,853
So let me add that.

47
00:02:26,853 --> 00:02:30,060
Along with that, other thing that we have to do

48
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:32,640
is this particular view component

49
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:36,240
must inherit from ViewComponent.

50
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:38,783
And, again, this is ViewComponent, not ViewComponents.

51
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:42,693
We have to add that using statement.

52
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:47,400
Now, this will be the backend file for our view component,

53
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,583
so we need to think about what we want to do here.

54
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:55,020
We basically have to go to the shopping cart database

55
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:58,590
and get the shopping cart for a logged-in user.

56
00:02:58,590 --> 00:03:01,140
So we need to inject unitOfWork,

57
00:03:01,140 --> 00:03:04,443
and we can do that using dependency injection.

58
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:09,090
Then inside here, we will create a method that will handle

59
00:03:09,090 --> 00:03:12,213
the backend functionality for our ShoppingCartViewComponent.

60
00:03:13,894 --> 00:03:18,894
It will return async Task, I can call it IActionResult,

61
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:22,140
but we know it will be a view component,

62
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:26,220
so we can directly say IViewComponentResult.

63
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:28,710
That will be the return type.

64
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:32,010
Now, the name of the function will be InvokeAsync,

65
00:03:32,010 --> 00:03:34,080
and that is what will be used

66
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:36,540
when we invoke the view component

67
00:03:36,540 --> 00:03:40,380
which we will see in the upcoming videos.

68
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:43,530
So name of the method here is InvokeAsync,

69
00:03:43,530 --> 00:03:46,470
and there, we need to retrieve the userId

70
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:48,797
of the logged-in user.

71
00:03:48,797 --> 00:03:53,700
Let me go and open the Areas, Controller.

72
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,760
We have Customer, HomeController.

73
00:03:56,760 --> 00:04:01,760
Let me copy this code right here. Cut that from the index.

74
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:04,503
Paste it right here.

75
00:04:07,451 --> 00:04:10,770
Now, right here, if the claim is not null,

76
00:04:10,770 --> 00:04:13,800
we are getting the session and setting that.

77
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,870
Else, if the claim is null,

78
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:19,320
we can directly clear the session right here,

79
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:23,098
so HttpContext.Session.Clear.

80
00:04:23,098 --> 00:04:26,880
And that way, we do not have to do that in the Logout,

81
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:29,103
so I can remove that as well.

82
00:04:30,420 --> 00:04:34,560
Inside the Logout where we added the functionality,

83
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:37,440
we no longer require that.

84
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,749
Perfect. That looks good.

85
00:04:39,749 --> 00:04:41,970
Now, what we want to return here

86
00:04:41,970 --> 00:04:45,270
is the actual count to our view.

87
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:48,540
So here, we will say return back to the View,

88
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:49,920
and we need the count

89
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:54,820
that is inside HttpContext.Session.GetInt32

90
00:04:56,820 --> 00:04:58,113
SD.SessionCart.

91
00:04:59,746 --> 00:05:03,810
When we clear everything, it will be zero,

92
00:05:03,810 --> 00:05:07,263
so we can return back that integer value.

93
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,450
So now you can think

94
00:05:09,450 --> 00:05:12,060
about we are returning something to the View,

95
00:05:12,060 --> 00:05:14,100
and the model is an integer.

96
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,600
That looks good.

97
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:20,580
But where will we create the view of this ViewComponent?

98
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:22,320
Before we add that file,

99
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:26,100
I can make this code a little more elegant.

100
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:31,100
Right here, I can check if HttpContext.Session.GetInt32

101
00:05:34,439 --> 00:05:37,410
SD.SessionCart,

102
00:05:37,410 --> 00:05:39,420
if that is not null,

103
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:42,510
then basically we have a session that is loaded.

104
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:47,160
We do not have to go to database, so we can return that.

105
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:52,160
So return View, and we can return back that entity.

106
00:05:52,740 --> 00:05:54,390
But if that is null,

107
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:57,183
only then we have to retrieve that item.

108
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:02,340
So rather than that, let me make it if it is null,

109
00:06:02,340 --> 00:06:04,740
then we will set the session here.

110
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:08,580
Else, we do not want to set our session.

111
00:06:08,580 --> 00:06:12,543
We will directly return whatever is set in our session.

112
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:18,090
So, basically, the code behind for ViewComponent looks good.

113
00:06:18,090 --> 00:06:21,573
Let me add the frontend view in the next video.

